I'll bring you your main course.

1074
01:17:43,400 --> 01:17:45,698
- Well?
- I put it in the soup.

1075
01:17:45,769 --> 01:17:48,101
- The whole bottle?
- Every drop.

1076
01:17:48,172 --> 01:17:49,639
You angel.

1077
01:17:50,941 --> 01:17:52,306
You're bleeding.

1078
01:17:52,376 --> 01:17:55,834
A cook tried to cut off my tail
with a carving knife.

1079
01:17:56,146 --> 01:17:58,808
Look! The Grand High Witch
is eating the soup!

1080
01:18:02,586 --> 01:18:04,383
They all are.

1081
01:18:13,263 --> 01:18:14,594
Another roll, sir?

1082
01:18:14,665 --> 01:18:15,893
No, thanks.

1083
01:18:16,667 --> 01:18:18,032
I'd like some...

1084
01:18:21,338 --> 01:18:23,465
I'd like some black pepper, please.

1085
01:18:23,941 --> 01:18:25,533
- My God!
- What?

1086
01:18:26,076 --> 01:18:29,409
Bruno's father
is about to eat the soup, too.

1087
01:18:29,780 --> 01:18:30,940
- Stop him!
- Quick!

1088
01:18:31,015 --> 01:18:34,382
I agree, dear, it's been a nightmare.

1089
01:18:35,185 --> 01:18:36,982
At least we got some cress soup.

1090
01:18:37,955 --> 01:18:39,320
Don't touch it!

1091
01:18:39,857 --> 01:18:43,054
I told you she was a loony.
She's an absolute nutter!

1092
01:18:43,594 --> 01:18:45,494
Look at my bloody soup!

1093
01:18:45,729 --> 01:18:47,993
And all that stuff about Bruno!

1094
01:18:48,098 --> 01:18:50,931
Bruno has been turned into...

1095
01:18:51,001 --> 01:18:53,492
He has not been turned into a...

1096
01:18:53,570 --> 01:18:55,629
Yes, I have. Hello, Dad.

1097
01:19:03,247 --> 01:19:06,375
Don't worry, Dad. It isn't all bad...

1098
01:19:07,251 --> 01:19:09,446
...just so long as the cat doesn't get me.

1099
01:19:09,520 --> 01:19:10,680
Bruno.

1100
01:19:10,754 --> 01:19:13,382
No more school, no more homework.

1101
01:19:13,657 --> 01:19:15,750
I'll live in the kitchen cupboard.

1102
01:19:17,861 --> 01:19:19,351
This is a trick.

1103
01:19:19,797 --> 01:19:21,162
It's that whiskey.

1104
01:19:22,066 --> 01:19:22,998
Hello, Mum.

1105
01:19:25,102 --> 01:19:28,037
Would you like to know
who did this to Bruno?

1106
01:19:36,413 --> 01:19:37,641
It's working.

1107
01:19:47,024 --> 01:19:48,218
Let go of me!

1108
01:19:52,463 --> 01:19:55,694
<i>My Formula 86! Give me that spoon!</i>

1109
01:19:57,201 --> 01:19:59,192
That woman over there.

1110
01:20:01,805 --> 01:20:05,468
She is the Grand High Witch.

1111
01:20:08,679 --> 01:20:11,580
Grandma,
she needs more time to become a...

1112
01:20:13,984 --> 01:20:16,544
She did it to Bruno...

1113
01:20:17,888 --> 01:20:22,848
...and thousands of other children
before him.

1114
01:20:25,129 --> 01:20:26,426
Good evening.

1115
01:20:26,630 --> 01:20:29,121
You're doomed, old woman!

1116
01:20:29,900 --> 01:20:31,800
You're doomed forever!

1117
01:20:31,869 --> 01:20:33,200
It must work.

1118
01:20:33,303 --> 01:20:34,327
You.

1119
01:20:42,880 --> 01:20:44,347
This is it, Bruno.

1120
01:20:55,058 --> 01:20:56,116
Come on!

1121
01:20:56,393 --> 01:20:57,826
Get the mice!

1122
01:21:05,402 --> 01:21:06,835
One is a witch.

1123
01:21:07,871 --> 01:21:11,602
The most evil and appalling woman
in the world.

1124
01:21:12,075 --> 01:21:13,804
A loathsome...

1125
01:21:14,311 --> 01:21:16,711
...hideous disgrace!

1126
01:21:17,080 --> 01:21:18,513
Yeah, Grandma!

1127
01:21:18,682 --> 01:21:23,346
I'm not finished with you yet, old woman!

1128
01:21:23,620 --> 01:21:25,178
Next time!

1129
01:21:26,456 --> 01:21:28,117
No next time.

1130
01:21:28,258 --> 01:21:31,853
This time it's your turn.

1131
01:21:44,107 --> 01:21:45,699
Herbert, do something!

1132
01:21:45,776 --> 01:21:47,505
It's in your garment.

1133
01:21:47,578 --> 01:21:49,273
- Good night.
- Good night.

1134
01:21:52,516 --> 01:21:55,280
Get that brown one! No, the other one!

1135
01:21:57,421 --> 01:21:58,786
Look, it's her.

1136
01:22:00,290 --> 01:22:02,087
Get away from me!

1137
01:22:02,159 --> 01:22:03,956
Don't let her get away.

1138
01:22:04,528 --> 01:22:05,517
Get away!

1139
01:22:10,734 --> 01:22:12,429
Get me out of here!

1140
01:22:15,973 --> 01:22:18,203
Get out of my hotel!

1141
01:22:20,611 --> 01:22:21,805
Mr. Stringer.

1142
01:22:23,747 --> 01:22:27,478
There's an especially impetuous one
over there, under the water jug.

1143
01:22:27,551 --> 01:22:28,483
Thank you.

1144
01:22:28,552 --> 01:22:30,452
It's a pleasure.

1145
01:22:31,355 --> 01:22:32,447
Get away from me!

1146
01:22:32,522 --> 01:22:34,854
I tell you, get away from me!

1147
01:22:36,727 --> 01:22:38,354
Get away from me!

1148
01:22:51,341 --> 01:22:54,003
My mum's not very crazy about mice.

1149
01:22:54,311 --> 01:22:55,903
So I see.

1150
01:22:57,848 --> 01:22:59,247
Here is Bruno.

1151
01:23:00,284 --> 01:23:02,752
- Thank you.
- He needs to go on a diet.

1152
01:23:03,787 --> 01:23:06,221
Hi, Dad. Hi, Mum.

1153
01:23:06,290 --> 01:23:08,281
Stop it, dear. Stop it.

1154
01:23:08,692 --> 01:23:10,455
This is our Bruno.

1155
01:23:11,795 --> 01:23:14,525
Don't cry, Mum. You'll get used to me.

1156
01:23:17,167 --> 01:23:18,794
<i>Just a minute, Grandma.</i>

1157
01:23:18,902 --> 01:23:20,096
'Bye, Bruno.

1158
01:23:20,470 --> 01:23:21,528
'Bye.

1159
01:23:22,205 --> 01:23:23,934
Excuse me.

1160
01:23:26,209 --> 01:23:28,507
You always wanted me to lose weight.

1161
01:23:28,578 --> 01:23:30,671
Well, look at me now.

1162
01:23:39,222 --> 01:23:42,316
There. But I still don't understand.

1163
01:23:42,392 --> 01:23:43,757
I won't be long.

1164
01:23:50,334 --> 01:23:51,699
Come on, this way.

1165
01:23:51,802 --> 01:23:53,702
Right to the main dining room.

1166
01:23:54,137 --> 01:23:55,126
Hurry up.

1167
01:23:55,205 --> 01:23:57,036
- Your taxi, madam.
- Good-bye.

1168
01:24:24,102 --> 01:24:25,501
Put it down, Bill.

1169
01:24:26,037 --> 01:24:27,766
- That's it.
- You all right?

1170
01:24:30,575 --> 01:24:32,372
- Can you manage?
- I'm fine.

1171
01:24:32,443 --> 01:24:34,172
Look out. There's a step.

1172
01:24:37,548 --> 01:24:38,981
- Mrs. Evershim?
- Yes.

1173
01:24:39,050 --> 01:24:41,177
- There's a trunk for you.
- A trunk?

1174
01:24:42,086 --> 01:24:44,554
- Will you sign for it?
- Yes, all right.

1175
01:24:45,123 --> 01:24:46,283
Come in.

1176
01:24:47,692 --> 01:24:49,626
Great! It's arrived.

1177
01:24:49,994 --> 01:24:52,258
Don't open it yet. Wait for me.

1178
01:24:52,563 --> 01:24:54,394
Put it down there. That'll do fine.

1179
01:24:54,465 --> 01:24:55,830
All right, ma'am.

1180
01:24:56,267 --> 01:24:57,359
That's it.

1181
01:24:58,936 --> 01:25:00,096
Here I come.

1182
01:25:01,572 --> 01:25:02,937
Thank you.

1183
01:25:03,007 --> 01:25:05,999
I still have no idea who it could be from.

1184
01:25:06,778 --> 01:25:08,973
This is really gonna surprise you.

1185
01:25:11,916 --> 01:25:12,974
Open it.

1186
01:25:13,785 --> 01:25:15,514
- But what is it?
- Open it.

1187
01:25:17,722 --> 01:25:18,916
Money!

1188
01:25:20,224 --> 01:25:22,658
I saw it in the Grand High Witch's room.

1189
01:25:22,727 --> 01:25:25,696
I figured we could use it
when we go to America.

1190
01:25:27,965 --> 01:25:29,193
America?

1191
01:25:29,901 --> 01:25:31,801
We've got to go home because...

1192
01:25:32,437 --> 01:25:33,426
Look!

1193
01:25:35,907 --> 01:25:37,636
It was the Grand High Witch's.

1194
01:25:37,708 --> 01:25:40,905
It has the name and address
of every witch in America.

1195
01:25:48,453 --> 01:25:50,648
You are a genius.

1196
01:25:56,127 --> 01:26:00,564
"It doesn't matter who you are
and what you are

1197
01:26:00,631 --> 01:26:02,963
"As long as somebody loves you"

1198
01:26:04,068 --> 01:26:04,864
Luke.

1199
01:26:04,936 --> 01:26:06,426
What a day.

1200
01:26:07,438 --> 01:26:10,134
Perhaps we could find a good witch...

1201
01:26:10,208 --> 01:26:12,233
...to turn you back into my grandson.

1202
01:26:12,310 --> 01:26:15,507
I'll never be able to drive a real car, will I?

1203
01:26:16,047 --> 01:26:17,309
I don't know.

1204
01:26:17,448 --> 01:26:19,245
How long do mice live?

1205
01:26:19,550 --> 01:26:23,077
I hope we have time to take on
those American witches.

1206
01:26:24,055 --> 01:26:25,386
Shall we go to New York?

1207
01:26:25,456 --> 01:26:27,287
I've never been to New York.

1208
01:26:31,729 --> 01:26:33,287
Can we travel by ship?

1209
01:26:33,965 --> 01:26:35,660
First class.

1210
01:26:35,933 --> 01:26:37,264
The best cabin.

1211
01:26:37,535 --> 01:26:39,799
The best of everything.

1212
01:26:43,174 --> 01:26:44,801
Good night, Grandma.

1213
01:26:46,043 --> 01:26:47,408
Good night, Luke.

1214
01:26:59,657 --> 01:27:02,353
I really am happy to be a mouse,
you know.

1215
01:27:04,328 --> 01:27:06,762
I know, my darling.

1216
01:27:53,911 --> 01:27:55,173
Grandma!

1217
01:27:56,480 --> 01:27:58,209
Grandma, what's happening?

1218
01:28:40,791 --> 01:28:44,090
Off you go, back home to Luke.

1219
01:28:47,465 --> 01:28:49,330
Look, they're back!

1220
01:28:56,974 --> 01:28:59,067
Don't forget Bruno!

1221
01:29:00,067 --> 01:29:10,067
